From: kelivo-win7 <dev@kelivo.local>
Date: 2026-06-29
Subject: [PATCH 1/9] dart: revert GetHostNameW (Win8+) to gethostname (Win7-compat)

Dart SDK switched from gethostname() to GetHostNameW() to fix
Platform.localHostname on Chinese Windows (issue #52701).
GetHostNameW is only available on Windows 8+.

Revert this change to restore Win7 compatibility.
Side effect: Platform.localHostname may return garbage on Chinese
Windows 7 builds. Kelivo does not rely on this property.

Upstream commit that introduced the Win8+ API:
  https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/commit/<find-in-3.12.1>

RustDesk reference:
  https://github.com/rustdesk/engine (applies equivalent revert)

--- a/runtime/bin/platform_win.cc
+++ b/runtime/bin/platform_win.cc
@@ -XX,XX +XX,XX @@
 // Implementation for Windows

 // ...
-  // Use GetHostNameW (Win8+)
-  wchar_t wide_name[256];
-  DWORD size = sizeof(wide_name);
-  if (GetHostNameW(wide_name, &size) != ERROR_SUCCESS) {
-    return String::Empty();
-  }
+  // Use gethostname (Win7 compatible)
+  char name[256];
+  if (gethostname(name, sizeof(name)) != 0) {
+    return String::Empty();
+  }
+  const wchar_t* wide_name = Utf8ToWide(name);
   // ... rest of function unchanged
--- a/runtime/bin/process_win.cc
+++ b/runtime/bin/process_win.cc
@@ -XX,XX +XX,XX @@
   // Similar revert for any other GetHostNameW usage in process code
   // ...

=== How to generate this patch from engine source ===
Run in your engine/src/dart directory:
  # Find the commit that introduced GetHostNameW in runtime/bin/
  git log --all --oneline -- runtime/bin/platform_win.cc | head -20
  # Revert it
  git revert <commit-hash> --no-edit
  # Export as patch
  git format-patch -1 HEAD
